{"word":"H7401 - רָכַךְ - râkak - raw-kak' - Faint","slug":"H7401","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">רָכַךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>râkak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>raw-kak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Faint"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E8;&#x05DB;&#x05DA; - ra&#x0302;kak</b> - <i>raw-kak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>soften</i> (intransitively or transitively), used figuratively: - (be) faint ([-hearted]), mollify, (be, make) soft (-er), be tender."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4816\">H4816</a>, <a href=\"#/H7390\">H7390</a>, <a href=\"#/H7391\">H7391</a>"}]}